**Tests:**
- Legacy YAML (no `retros:` block) → `w.Retros == nil`, `w.OnRunCloseEnabled() == true`, all other trigger accessors false, no validation error.
- `ParseYAML(legacy).YAML()` round-trips BYTE-STABLE: re-encoding a legacy workflow.yaml that has no `retros:` produces NO spurious `retros:` block (assert bytes equal input / assert no "retros" substring).
- `retros:` block PRESENT with `on_run_close` omitted → `w.Retros != nil` (presence preserved) AND `w.OnRunCloseEnabled() == true` (effective default).
- Explicit `on_run_close: false` honored → `w.OnRunCloseEnabled() == false`.
- Automated-trigger-without-generator → ErrInvalidWorkflow, but ONLY for an explicit block (e.g. block with `on_failed_verify: true` and no generator errors; an ABSENT block never errors even though on_run_close is effectively true).
- `on_repeated_gate_block.enabled: true`, threshold omitted → `w.RepeatedGateBlockThreshold() == 3`, valid; threshold `0` → error; threshold `>= 1` → valid.
- KnownFields rejects an unknown key inside `retros:` AND inside nested `on_repeated_gate_block:`.
- `Default().YAML()` golden bytes UNCHANGED (existing test still passes — `Default()` leaves `Retros == nil`, omitted).
- Explicit-block round-trip stable: parse→encode→parse of an authored block (with some fields set, some omitted) yields an equal struct and equal bytes (omitted fields stay omitted).
- Manual-only / all-automated-off explicit block: a present block with `on_run_close: false` and every other trigger false → no generator required (no error).

**Docs:**
- docs/init.md — the only user-facing doc describing the scaffolded workflow.yaml shape ("What it creates"). Add a short `retros:` schema subsection documenting the block, the default-on `on_run_close` (effective both when the block is absent and when present-with-omitted-field), the opt-in triggers, the generator-required-when-an-explicit-block-enables-automation rule (and that omitting the block entirely keeps legacy/Default valid), and the advisory/non-gating nature. Cross-reference docs/plans/product/etude-retro-command.md §4.
- `make docs-reality` / `make docs-check` are NOT triggered: both guard the CLI command surface (generated docs/cli pages + README command mentions). This bead adds no command and changes no command surface, so the CLI docs guards do not apply. (Noted explicitly so the gate does not expect a docs/cli change.)

**Risks:** Low. Additive, optional field following the existing `Eval *Eval` optional-pointer convention. The accessor model removes the round-trip and presence-bit hazards of the earlier synthesize-on-absent approach: `Retros == nil` ⇔ absent, defaults are computed on read, the struct is never mutated, so legacy YAML re-encodes byte-stable and the generator-required rule is correctly gated on an explicit block. No consumers break: the only external readers are internal/cli/init.go (uses Default()/ParseYAML; Default() leaves Retros nil) — adding an optional field + read accessors is backward compatible.

**Gate tier:** Tier 1. The review-gate runbook (docs/plans/dogfood/review-gate-runbook.md:25) lists "workflow ... schema/format ... changes" as a Tier 1 trigger. Although this change is additive + optional + advisory (no gating, no storage write), it modifies the workflow schema and future compatibility of .etude/workflow.yaml, which is squarely the runbook's letter. Recommend Tier 1; the gate holds the runbook's text.

